You can declare a default final method in an interface in groovy. Thereby you can define a method body in an interface and prevent implementing classes to override this method. 

However unlike to a static method, you will need an instance to call this method.
``` groovy
interface Example {
    default final void myMethodWithBody() {
        // do something
    }
}
